      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of cosmic insignificance is a profound, ancient human thought. Many philosophers grapple with this perceived meaninglessness, contrasting existential dread with the value found in subjective experience. Perhaps the point isn't a grand, universal purpose, but the way we connect, create, and find meaning within our brief, conscious lives. In that personal struggle and connection, a valuable, temporary reality is forged.",
      "source": "target",
